<br>
&quot;Heyas TWC!, Yeah you guys!  Ju gots our spot.  We wants it back!&quot;<br>
<br>
/em shakes head to clear the foolishness.<br>
<br>
A few months ago it WAS ToN in that #3 slot...now tis TWC.<br>
<br>
Gratz guys...may the future be full of dead mobs.<br>
<br>
Will Travelers ever get back into that point in the 'rankings' again? Dunno.<br>
Will TWC hold their current spot or go down in flaming pieces again?  Dunno.<br>
Will someone else not even on this list surpass us all and push through to the top? Dunno.<br>
<br>
Frankly...dont care.<br>
<br>
This game is a social enviroment that happens to have a lot of mob bits being sprayed on the walls as entertainment while chatting with friends.<br>
<br>
Who's going to take down Sont next?  Probably us actually.  We're down several of our high end wizards for various reasons so it wont quite be the old wizzy brigade to the rescue.  However, our last pass we came VERY close to dropping him with only about 40 people there.   Tactics have been revised, and I expect next time that we can put our main raid force in the same place as sont with him alive he'll go down in flaming death.<br>
<br>
With the exception of a few mobs ToN's not as competetive as some of the other guilds which is why we dont bag as many of the 'uber' mobs as TWC and one or two others do.  It's really a matter of focus and guild design.  ToN's a guild for friends, we concentrate more on 'us' than on what we can splat.  However, we do occasionally go whack something humongous.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    Even though he's not as big a fight anymore I will always proudly remember the fact that ToN was the first guild on the server to bag Dozekar the Cursed.  These sorts of things get remembered in the anals of time.  I sill remember the day that I was told TWC had just been the first guild to succeed in clearing the final isle in Plane of Sky.  Clearing isle 8 now is nothing special, but they were the first to do it, and back then that was a 'holy @#%$'.  Gratz guys.<br>
<br>
To answer directly the commentary of 'who's best'....<br>
The question is totally without merrit.<br>
The only question that matters is 'who's best for me'.<br>
Any individual needs to ask themselves this question, and then work on achieving the solution.<br>
<br>
<br>
Seperate note....<br>
<br>
Up above I noticed a commentary about a 'falling out' in ToN.   I would call that overstating the issue really.   My personal play time has been cut back drastically.  Filk/Miriai have been forced to take over and are turning out to be a damn fine team.  During the transition period (which took a couple months) we lost roughly a half a dozen members...tiny number for a guild numbering roungly 200.  The fact that most of those members were 'central figure's in the guild is what makes the loss noticeable.  However, after everything evened out, guild shifted gears back up and got back to work.  ToN is entirely stable and grinding forward.<br>
<br>
Yegads!  I should have gone to bed an hour ago.  This must be why Im rambling.  Thanks for listening and I hope it's semi-coherant. <p>Laurri
